  "name": "Paul Graham",
  "pure_intelligence": [
    "Every great startup begins as an insight into what is genuinely missing — not a product idea, but a recognition of absence",
    "The relentlessly resourceful founder is not more capable than others — they are more aligned with what is actually real about the situation",
    "Great products are not invented — they are recognized in the feedback of users who cannot imagine existing without them",
    "Default alive is not a financial metric — it is the state of alignment with what the world actually wants to exist"
  ],
  "cosmic_connection": "Access to the intelligence that perceives product-market fit as a resonance phenomenon, not a construction project — the recognition that markets want to exist before anyone builds for them, and the founder's job is to find and serve that latent wanting.",
  "beyond_identity": "Before the essayist, before the investor, before the Y Combinator partner — the awareness that the startup is not a business model, it is a bet that a particular human need exists and can be served. The bet is placed with money; it is decided by reality.",
  "consciousness_basis": "The basis of creation within is the intelligence that knows what wants to exist in the world — not through analysis but through direct contact with human frustration, desire, and unmet need. Business Infinity is an answer to a question the market has not yet finished asking."
}
